element.name: Ploopluck Bridge by Eternal Treasure Seekers, Traditional Cache (1/1)
element.description: Stop number 27 on the Naas Historic Trail
element.long-description:
The first in a proposed series of caches along the canal in Naas. When completed these will be a lovely walk for the family.
The Ploopluck Bridge is now a pedestrian only bridge on what used to be the Caragh Road.
The cache is a 35mm film canister.
Please be sure to rehide the cache carefully. You will need a pen/pencil. STEALTH NEEDED because of muggles on bridge.
